# Pin line endings to LF on every platform, on disk and in the index.
#
# Without this file the repo is at the mercy of each contributor's
# `core.autocrlf` setting: Windows checkouts get CRLF in the working tree,
# Linux/macOS checkouts get LF, and tools that emit LF directly (editors,
# code generators, this project's automation) trigger the
# "LF will be replaced by CRLF the next time Git touches it" warning on
# every commit. Five files in this tree had ended up with *mixed* line
# endings (partial LF, partial CRLF) by the time this attributes file was
# added — that's a real correctness hazard for shell scripts and patch
# tools.
#
# `* text=auto eol=lf` says:
#   - Detect text vs binary automatically (same as `text=auto` alone).
#   - For text files: store LF in the index AND check out LF in the
#     working tree on every platform, regardless of `core.autocrlf` or
#     `core.eol`. This file's directives override those settings.
#
# Binary files that happen to be detected as text (or that we want to
# pin as binary regardless of content sniffing) are listed below.

* text=auto eol=lf

# ── Binaries ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Never apply line-ending or whitespace normalization to these.
*.png      binary
*.jpg      binary
*.jpeg     binary
*.gif      binary
*.ico      binary
*.icns     binary
*.bmp      binary
*.svg      binary
*.pdf      binary
*.zip      binary
*.tar      binary
*.tar.gz   binary
*.tgz      binary
*.bz2      binary
*.xz       binary
*.7z       binary
*.gz       binary
*.zst      binary
*.wasm     binary
*.bvplugin binary
*.bvx      binary
*.bvbk     binary
*.crt      binary
*.cer      binary
*.der      binary
*.p12      binary
*.pfx      binary
*.woff     binary
*.woff2    binary
*.ttf      binary
*.otf      binary
*.eot      binary
*.mp3      binary
*.mp4      binary
*.webm     binary
*.webp     binary

# ── Generated files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Lock files are text but should not be diffed in PR reviews; mark them
# linguist-generated so GitHub collapses them.
Cargo.lock         linguist-generated
gui/package-lock.json linguist-generated
